Hand/Eye Coordination: Something about it was completely unnatural. Corrupted. Your muscle memory knew what to do and went for it, but there were gaps...
Physical Instrument: Yeah! Gaps you tried to fill with *thinking*. We don't *think* in sports. We *DO*!
René Arnoux: "A fine example you are setting here today, officer." He says, slowly shaking his head. "I will remember this. And Gaston will too."

Gaston Martin: "It's okay, officer. Forgotten completely. It was my *boule* and I have a spare." He produces another ball from his pocket. "Everything is good and we're ready to assist any way we can!"
Jump to: [Suggestion: "Just talk. It'll smooth things over..."]
René Arnoux: "*Merde*!" the old soldier yells in outrage. "*Bordel de merde*!!!"
Esprit de Corps: It's your refusal to take responsibility I don't like.
René Arnoux: "*Mon dieu*..." he mumbles, rubbing his temples. "Alright. Alright. Fine. What do you want, officer?"
Rhetoric: Yes... why *did* you come here? It's unlikely they know anything about the murder.

Hand/Eye Coordination: This felt... wrong. Wrong like touching your sister's breast. You threw your sister's breast.
René Arnoux: "You vandalized our game, son." He tries to calm himself. "We can't play pétanque with five *boules*."
Hand/Eye Coordination: You are immediately surprised by the ball's lack of weight. No matter. You'll make it work.
Electrochemistry: God, this is right -- you feel the familiar tremble of excitement and adrenaline that precedes every victory. Time has frozen.
You: "Sorry, an honest mistake. Are we good?"
René Arnoux: "No, we are not *good*, goddamnit!" A vein on his forehead is bulging alarmingly. "We want our *boule* back!"
Half Light: He's trying to avoid conflict at any cost.
René Arnoux: IsKimHere()
You: "I don't have a *boule*, but will this do?" (Hold out the shot put ball.)
René Arnoux: "Will this...." He falls silent and stares at the ball. "No, it will *goddamn* not..."
ahub
You: "Perfect throw? Well, I still feel defeated."
You: There is time for a last glance inward. Who am I?
You: Let go. Be the ball. (Continue.)
The inertia can be contained no more than a bullet leaving a gun. Let go. Be the bullet. (Continue.)
You: Feel the ball.
Composure: Look who's talking -- that cockatoo uniform must give him a real advantage. When fighting in *the circus*.

Hand/Eye Coordination: It felt like you were going for a thrust or a lunge -- there was definitely gonna be jumping. Maybe you scored a point, but this is a *fiasco*.
You: Hold on, why *did* it feel so wrong?
You: "I'm sensing anger. And I don't understand why."
You: "The damn ball was slippery as fuck! How do you expect me to throw this piece of *shit* when it's got old man spunk all over, Mossback?!"
Gaston Martin: "What are you talking about? You just executed a pretty much perfect pétanque throw!" His tone is full of admiration.
You: "I was going for something cool, but I screwed it up, like always..."
René Arnoux: The man in the uniform says nothing. His gaze is fixed on the horizon.

IsKimHere()

Perception (Hearing): Everything has gone very quiet. It seems as even the waves have ceased their crashing against the promenade. It feels heavy.
René Arnoux: IsKimHere()

Hand/Eye Coordination: The cold metal ball is surprisingly smooth against your neck. It has a pattern on it. (Probably a sponsored ball.) Yours would only be covered with bumps of learning and scars of victory.
Hand/Eye Coordination: Already your muscles are adjusting to the weight, the nervous system calibrating, until you and the ball have merged into a single entity. The *manball* is ready.
You: "Okay, I will try to fix this." (Accept the task.)
René Arnoux: "Good." He nods. "Mistakes are forgiven, when men at least *try* to right their wrongs. I believe you will try. Now why did you approach us?"
You: Take in the surroundings.

Hand/Eye Coordination: A chilly breeze ruffles your hair as you stand there, feet firmly planted. All sounds, smells, even the wind -- everything fades until the only thing left is the union of Man and Ball.

René Arnoux: "Spring slush on bare feet can make a man feel like a failure." He points at your naked toes. "For a reason. Now, do you need something from us?"

You: "I thought it was shot-put."
René Arnoux: "Well, it damn well isn't, it's pétanque," the man snaps, raising his voice again. "You ruined a pétanque game. We want our *boule* back!"
René Arnoux: "Probably because those rooster pants are squeezing you senseless. What ever happened to practical? Durable? Revachol-made?" He shakes his head. "Now what can I do for you?"

René Arnoux: "How are you ever going to get the officer's shit off your nose, Gaston? Or even climb out of his ass?" He shakes his head in extreme disdain.
You: "That's just how Johnny Ballgame is -- extraordinary."

Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant says nothing, but his face is rigid. It seems he does not approve of your athletic displays.
Gaston Martin: "Thank you, officer." The jolly man quickly takes the ball and bounces it in his hand. "This is really something... Honestly I think it's better than our old *boule* even!"

Kim Kitsuragi: "Yes, officer..." The lieutenant gives you a quick side-glance. "What *do* we need from these gentlemen?"
You: "I'm sorry."
René Arnoux: "Your guess is as good as mine, officer. Maybe you're just one of those men who's never satisfied with anything?" He shrugs. "Regardless, what do you need from us?"

Shivers: West, in the Grand Couron Arena, a sharp overhand left from Arsène-Luc Edelbrock, sends the Samaran heavyweight champion, Kostya 'Mjasnok' Koštunica, flying to the mat. The crowd goes wild. Revachol loves her heroes.
René Arnoux: "What the HELL is your problem?"
You: "Not a weak right triceps, that's for sure."
You: "I'm a god of track and field. Why would I have a problem with anything?"
René Arnoux: "No, no you don't! Our pétanque game is ruined!" He's getting angry again. "We want our *boule* back."
Gaston Martin: "Take it easy, René." The jolly one tries to defuse the situation. "This is just a misunderstanding, isn't it, officer? No harm done."
You: "Wait... what?"

Gaston Martin: His merry partner is staring at the ground like he's trying to see right through to the other side.
Authority: You are an officer of the law with way more important things to worry about than *boules*. Don't take this crap.
You: "Listen, guys, the ball is gone, and I have a murder to solve, alright?" (Refuse task.)
René Arnoux: "Right," the old soldier says slowly. "Was the demonstration *it*, or do you still need something from us, officer?"
Esprit de Corps: *Some* would still say you're a cop, but I guess we're beyond that now.
You: "The throw was terrible and you know it. No need to mock me."
Hand/Eye Coordination: An embodiment of pure motion. A fine-tuned *locomotor* running at maximum efficiency.
